parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake lines can cause sudden and complete brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaks
ABS light comes on
pulsing or hesitation when braking
loss of braking power
and increased stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause increased stopping distance, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: ABS light comes on
pulsing or hesitation when braking
loss of braking power
and increased stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC blower motor resistor can cause the blower motor to overheat, leading to a fire hazard, and loss of visibility due to windshield icing or fogging.
symptoms: The blower motor stops working
smoke or a burning smell is present
and the wiring harness may be melted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
and the airbag deploys unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire hazard, loss of vehicle control, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
causing the headlights
taillights
or interior lights to fail
and the wiring harness may be melted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The key can be removed from the ignition with the engine running
and the ignition switch may be stuck in the "on" position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seat heater can cause a fire hazard and injuries.
symptoms: The seat heater comes on unexpectedly and cannot be turned off
causing a burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip, or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips
hesitates
or loses power
the vehicle has difficulty shifting gears
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle has a hard time accelerating
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake lines are rusted or leaking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power or have difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transfer case makes unusual noises
the transfer case warning light comes on
the vehicle has difficulty shifting gears
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front differential can cause the vehicle to vibrate or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The front differential makes unusual noises
the front differential vibrates
the vehicle loses power.
